overview: The user requested a thorough review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all acceptance criteria outlined in the provided
  specification. The agent conducted a detailed analysis, identifying several
  missing features and areas for improvement. Subsequently, the agent
  implemented a critical 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, including safety
  warnings for high scores. Detection and recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia
  and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome were added. The
  report was enhanced with a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps" section
  containing placeholder outbound links to relevant sleep and mental health
  organizations. Additionally, the scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness
  (EDS) was updated to incorporate weighted values for specific activities,
  providing a more accurate severity assessment. Five out of eight planned tasks
  were completed during this session.
